<br>
      If you noticed the story completion percentage as you have played you need to get 100% to see the perfect ending. There is also something you need to do to trigger the ending by pressing x during one of the scenes. Of course i needed to go buy the strategy guide for the game because you have to do 8 million obscure things to achieve this. In the other games they just had one ending and all the extra added stuff was to get the best weapons/armor/ items in the game. This time they decided to add all that stuff in to get the good ending :/.<br>
<br>
     Just finished chapter one last night getting all the scenes. My suggestion is you will need to go buy the guide or wait for someone to post an american version walkthrough on the internet. Anyway thought I would let you know so, you dont feel too robbed, although you still may feel a little robbed knowing you are going to have to wait 6 months or shell out the 15 dollars for the guide.<br>
<br>
